~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
Guild Rules of Fyrelake Guardians, Adaptable to your Guild.<br>
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
<br>
1) Groups will not &quot;jump&quot; over &quot;invis past&quot; or threaton to take a wing named mob from another group.<br>
<br>
2) Groups will not pressure another group to move faster to take said named.<br>
<br>
3) Groups and individual group members will be cordial and speak with the other group and ask if they can be of assistance.   If assistance is requested they will decide how to distribute any loots or drops.<br>
<br>
4) Groups will be given the opportunity to clean themselves up after wipes before another group attempts to move past them.<br>
   <br>
    A) If communication between groups is not capable, bodies of the wiped group must be in graveyard before your group may attempt a wing named.<br>
<br>
    B) Group leaders can ask if the group needs assistance and work together to take said named, or get *clarification* that the group that had wiped will not be attempting to take named again.<br>
<br>
    C) Groups will allow the opportunity for the group that had wiped to try again if they wish, without pressure or threats.<br>
<br>
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
<br>
This is a summary of basic guidelines of fairplay.   This isnt your guidelines this is our guidelines that we follow.   Various instances that &quot;I&quot; I have been in have called for these rules to be in effect for us.<br>
<br>
This is a suggestion that you and other players of Saryrn should take into consideration.<br>
<br>
Grundge Grumbles<br>
